function info=BlitBitImage(windowPtr,bitImage,imageSize,imageSeq,...                           [nframes],[theCluts],[rect],[checkAbort],[bits])% info=BlitBitImage(windowPtr,bitImage,imageSize,imageSeq,...%                    [nframes],[theCluts],[rect],[checkAbort],[bits])%% OBSOLETE - Use SCREEN instead. See MovieDemo.% % Displays sequence of images in the specified window at frame rate.%% "bitImage" contains a sequence of images created by InsertBitImage or% InsertBitImage255. "imageSize" is the size of each image. "imageSeq"% holds a list of images to be shown. For example, using imageSeq=[1:n]% shows the first n images in order.  If an entry of imageSeq is negative,% the CLUT is changed to the indexed CLUT on that frame.  In this case,% tha argument "theCluts" must be passed. "nframes" is the total number of% frames to be played. The sequence will repeat until nframes is reached. % If nframes is not passed, the sequence will be displayed once.% % On return, info(1) contains the number of frames shown, info(2) contains% the time to show those frames in secs.  Timing is done with Pelli's% VideoToolbox timer routines.% % See also: ZeroBitImage, InsertBitImage255, InsertBitImage.